cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on understanding the receptive fields of units in deep convolutional neural networks, which is a key aspect of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of various architectural choices on the effective receptive field, such as nonlinear activations (cs.NE), dropout (cs.LG), and skip connections (cs.AI). The paper also touches on the use of convolutional neural networks for natural language processing (cs.CL), although this is a relatively minor aspect of the paper.
